Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_voltage_scaling(25.10)                    report_voltage_scaling(25.10)

Name
       report_voltage_scaling  - Reports instances whose timing data is inter-
       polated due to voltage mismatch

Syntax
       report_voltage_scaling

       [-help]

       [<objectListOrCollection>]

       [-analysis_type {early | late}]

       [-view <string>]

       [-output_file <string>]

       Reports instances whose timing data is interpolated due to voltage mis-
       match. When a cell is operating in the design at  a  voltage  different
       from voltages at which it is characterized in the timing libraries, de-
       lay  calculation (DC) interpolates/derives the timing data at the oper-
       ating voltage.

Parameters
       -analysis_type {early | late}
              Specifies whether early or late views have  to  be  checked  for
              voltage scaling. If unspecified, only `late' views are checked.

       -output_file <string>
              Specifies  the  name of the output file to which the report will
              be written. When the specified file name  contains  a  directory
              path,  the  directory hierarchy is automatically created, if not
              present. If this option is not specified, the report is  written
              to standard output (screen).

       <objectListOrCollection>
              Specifies  the name(s) or a collection of leaf-level instance(s)
              for which voltage scaling needs to be checked and  reported.  If
              not specified, all instances of the design are checked.

       -view <string>
              Specify  the  name(s) of view(s) to be checked for voltage scal-
              ing. If unspecified, all active analysis views are checked.

Examples
       The following example shows a sample report_voltage_scaling report:

       tempus  2  >  report_voltage_scaling  i_6  -analysis_type  late   -view
       func_worst_cmax

       VIEW: func_worst_cmax -- ANALYSIS TYPE: late

       <pin-name>  :  <cell-name> : <actual-voltage> : <low-lib-name> : <high-
       lib-name>

       i_6/Y      : BUFX5MTH    : 0.820            : elc_08v        : elc_09v

       The report is generated with the func_worst_cmax view. You can use  the
       -view parameter to report for other views.

       You can run the report_analysis_views command to list views.

